org.openehealth.ipf.commons.flow.history

Class SplitHistory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openehealth.ipf.commons.flow.history.SplitHistory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<SplitHistory>

    public class SplitHistory
extends Object
implements Comparable<SplitHistory>, Serializable
    Tracks the split history of a message. Message splits are represented by SplitHistoryEntrys. Each message split adds a new SplitHistoryEntry to a message's split history. An aggregation of previously split messages removes SplitHistoryEntrys from those messages. Split-aggregate pairs are therefore not visible in a message's split history. A split history containing only the SplitHistoryEntry.ROOT entry means that the message hasn't been split yet (or an aggregation compensated the first split).
    Author:
    Martin Krasser
